 -- Darren Salt <linux@youmustbejoking.demon.co.uk>  Sun, 07 Mar 2010 00:00:21 +0000

xine-lib (1.1.17-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release.
    - Fixes the upstream part of the FTBFS on Hurd. (Closes: #530796)
    - Gapless playback fixes. (Closes: #467110)
    - Supports Matroska chapters. (Closes: #515212)
    - No longer truncates catalog.cache. This fixes problems with failure to
      recognise supported media types. (Closes: #523859)
  * Build-depend on libvcdinfo-dev, fixing libcdio static linkage.
    (Closes: #537078)
  * Convert to source format 3.0 (quilt), with adaptations for Mercurial
    queue usage.

  [Marc Dequènes]
  * Arch-specific install files generation for GNU/Hurd (similar to
    kfreebsd-i386). (Ref. #530796)

 -- Darren Salt <linux@youmustbejoking.demon.co.uk>  Tue, 01 Dec 2009 13:01:32 +0000

xine-lib (1.1.16.3-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Patches pulled from upstream:
    - Port to new libmpcdec API; fix FTBFS. (Closes: #476374, #552957)
    - Fix FTBFS on the Hurd. (Closes: #530976)
    - Fix a minor POSIX incompatibility (PATH_MAX usage).
    - Fix seeking in large raw DV files. (Closes: #531365)
    - Add advisory nos. for the (previously-fixed) QT demuxer bug.
    - Atomically replace catalog.cache when rewriting it.
      (Closes: #448440, #487582)
    - Incorrect int-to-float conversion in the JACK output plugin.
    - Fix parsing of ID3 tag content lengths.
    - Fix a possible ffmpeg-related segfault at end-of-stream.
    - Make "dvb://" work with the default configuration.
    - xine(5): clarify MRL encoding requirements.
  * Bump standards version to 3.8.3; tighten libxine-dev's dependency on
    libxine1-bin.
  * Fix various lintian warnings:
    - postinst scripts ignoring errors
  * "Fix" /usr/share/doc symlink without dependency by overriding (for now).
    (Intent is to fix properly post-squeeze.)

 -- Darren Salt <linux@youmustbejoking.demon.co.uk>  Sun, 01 Nov 2009 01:34:58 +0000

xine-lib (1.1.16.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

  [ Darren Salt ]
  * New upstream release.
    - Fix another possible int overflow in the 4XM demuxer.
      (ref. TKADV2009-004, CVE-2009-0698) (Closes: #517792)
    - Fix an integer overflow in the Quicktime demuxer.
    - Fix audio/video desynchronisation issues. (Closes: #521269)

  * Post-release patches from upstream:
    - Correct invalid MIME info in the MOD demuxer.
    - Fix a resource leak in libdvdnav.
    - Properly NUL-terminate when reading ID3v2.2 tag content.
    - Fix calculation of length of UTF-16 content sourced from, e.g., ID3 tags.

  * Update the home page link in debian/control.
    xinehq.de is missing presumed 410, and we now have www.xine-project.org.
  * Update debian/copyright.
    The authors list is probably not complete, and is certainly not wrt
    AUTHORS, but the removed entries are relevant only to front ends.
  * Update copyright information somewhat.
    [WIP.]
  * Sync Section information with the archive – mostly. libxine1-console
    belongs in section "libs" since, like libxine1-x, it's required by some
    front ends; and libxine1-bin belongs there too, as it's required by other
    libxine1* packages.
  * Add dh_xine, for use when building front ends.
  * Don't build-depend on libmagick-dev since it can pull in
    graphicsmagick-libmagick-dev-compat, which causes the image decoder
    plugin not to be built → FTBFS.

  [ Reinhard Tartler ]
  * Switch Maintainer/Uploaders fields.

 -- Darren Salt <linux@youmustbejoking.demon.co.uk>  Tue, 07 Apr 2009 16:45:40 +0100

xine-lib (1.1.16.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release.
    - All patches are present upstream.
    - Fixes a possible integer overflow in the 4XM demuxer.
      (TKADV2009-004, CVE-2009-0698)
    - Fixes problems with amarok, kaffeine and others. (Closes: #514114)

  [Darren Salt]
  * Import an upstream patch to fix pause/resume freeze problems with
    pulseaudio.
  * Use bzip2 for .deb compression.

  [Loic Minier]
  * Rework clean target to call $(MAKE) -f debian/rules unpatch after
    distclean instead of being a dep.  Also replace the numerous calls to
    dh_clean with a single one.
  * Use touch $@ to create stamps instead of repeating the target name.

